      "record_losses": "No known record losses. Among ND's OLDEST organized counties.",
      "jurisdictional_notes": "Created and organized 1867 — among the OLDEST organized counties in what became ND. Named for Pembina settlement (oldest European settlement in ND, est. 1797). Cavalier is county seat. Canadian border. Métis, French-Canadian, and Icelandic settlement. Red River Valley.",
      "research_tips": "FamilySearch and Pembina County Recorder (Cavalier). ND's first settled area — Pembina was the original Red River Settlement trading post (1797). Métis heritage is strong: check Hudson's Bay Company records and Manitoba Provincial Archives for cross-border families. St. Joseph's Catholic Church (Walhalla) has some of ND's oldest parish registers. Icelandic settlement at Akra and Mountain. Pembina County Historical Society in Cavalier. Pembina State Museum. SHSND microfilm for early territorial-era deeds and probate.",
      "heritage_book": null,
      "online_land_records_url": "https://www.pembinacountynd.gov/recorder",
      "online_land_records_earliest_year": 1867,
      "online_land_records_scope": "online portal — among ND's oldest"
